<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-063-199 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 238 071</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 9 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sony halts US workstations production. (Sony Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (Production management).andO;Product:   Sony News (Workstation) (Manufacture).andO;Topic:     WorkstationsCompetitionCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****SONY HALTS US WORKSTATIONS PRODUCTION 09/09/91 TOKYO, JAPAN, 1991 SEP 9(NB) -- Sony has stopped manufacturing its NEWS workstations in the U.S.andP;  dueto the declining profit and severe sales competition in the U.S.andP;  market.andM;Sony had converted its San Diego plant's TV set and CRT monitor productionlines to make workstations and was producing the NEWS units there since 1988.andO;Sony has stopped production of NEWS workstations at the plant, and is nowimporting the machines from Japan.andP;  Apparently, this is a cheaper route nowthat the 100-percent retaliatory tax against 32-bit Japanese computers hasbeen lifted.andM;Many computer makers including Sony have been having a hard time surviving inthe fiercely competitive US workstation market in the U.S.andP;  where firms likeSun Microsystems and Hewlett- Packard are strong.andP;  The Nikkei PersonalComputer magazine hints that Sony was not able to stop declining sales in theU.S.andP;  market.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910909/Press Contact: Sony, andplus;81-3-3448-2200)</TEXT></DOC>